title: so I turned to more inexpensive alternatives trying a pair here and there to find what ones I like that also give me rather decent quality
content: I bought these along with the (Betron YSM1000 Headphones) Seeing how my headphones have been chewed up by 4 dogs at home, or get stolen by staff or siblings.. Or simply lost on my part, I go through headphones lately rather quickly, so I turned to more inexpensive alternatives trying a pair here and there to find what ones I like that also give me rather decent quality, especially with the Bass... And I must say out of the 10 different pairs I've gone through over the last 2-3 months.. These are definitely what caught me off guard. I love em, even better than the other pair I got from Betron, Packaging was simple but sweet. But the sealing effect of the large pieces on this fit like a glove in my ear, really closing any gaps and keeping it locked in my ear. And the bass was what really set me, I spent recently $35+ on a pair of headphones that clamed to have some serious base but when I rocked those for a couple of weeks I realized it didn't have any to show for, but the moment I unboxed these after trying the other pair by these guys, this set really shocked me especially for the price.. Needless to say I've stuck with these for the last week or so and am loving it. Use it at work, and at home. Still preforming like a charm.

title: In-Ear Headphones that Feel Like a Live Performance
content: When my old earbuds stopped working in the middle of the night I needed to find a quick replacement. I rushed to the pharmacy and picked up a pair of Craig in-earbuds for $13. Not a premium choice, but how bad could they be? Little did I know; they were so bad I started thinking something might be wrong with my computer's audio system. So I visited "Ryan's" blog on the Midination website for his incredibly helpful and well-researched list of "The 24 best earbuds under $50". His entry on the betron DC950Hi caught my eye. These in-ear headphones were only $5 dollars more than the ones I bought at the pharmacy, but what a difference in quality these earbuds made! They provide a full range of sound and seem sturdy and well-built. Their noise-isolation is excellent, giving you a rich musical experience without distortion or distracting outside noises. I've tested these earbuds with classic rock, symphonic music, jazz, Hip Hop, and movies -- they deliver amazing sound. I have had $100 earbuds that can't compete with the betron DC950Hi. Plus, betron pays attention to the details: the gold-plated plug, the comfortable earbud gels, the flat tangle-free cable, and the convenient carrying pouch reflect the value consumers will find in this brand. I've decided to purchase two back-up pairs because I never want to have to rush to the pharmacy in the middle of the night and settle for in-ear earbuds that make it so that it's not even worth listening to the music at all. The DC950Hi puts me right there, in the music.

title: I wish I could give 6 stars!
content: If I could give these earphones 6 stars, I would.  These earphones have completely exceeded my expectations, and I would highly recommend them.  First, they have fantastic sound quality.  The audio hrz spanned by these earphones are fantastic.  Secondly, because the sound quality is so good and clear, I find that I can cut the volume in half of what I normally used to listen to on previous other earphones.  This is great, as I don't want to damage my ear by needing to turn up the volume to have a pleasurable listening experience.  I use these when I work out, in a noisy room.  I don't hear the sounds of the gym, and I don't have to turn up the volume of the earphones to 'drown' out other noise.  All the while, I get the great quality of the audio being played.  Third, I was perhaps a little concerned that the "bass driven" description would mean that there is too much bass in the audio mix.  That is definitely not the case.  The mix of bass, mids and treble are great.  I'm really pleased with it.  Indeed, these earphones CAPTURE the low tones, but they certainly do not overwhelm or throw the mix out of balance.  The best way to describe the sound quality, other than "really good", is to say it is very "full-bodied."  Again, I'm super pleased with this about the earphones.  Fourth, the "tangle free" feature of the cord is legitimate.  I haven't had one tangling issue yet, and I've used them a lot already.  It sucks fighting the cords; that isn't an issue with these earphones. In sum, I would absolutely recommend these earphones.  Too boot, the price is a steal.  I've never been more pleased spending $10 on a pair of earphones.  Betron got it right with these!

title: Great quality and presentation
content: I've been surprised by this earphones. For the pricepoint, the presentation of the earphones is great! It comes in a box with silicone tips of 3 sizes (s, m, l) and a medium size foam tips as bonus. The earphones look nice, are flat cable and even though I can't really tell if they will be durable because I've been using them for only 3 weeks in the office, they appear to be durable for this price and good quality. They look as if they are of a higher price, with coworkers asking that they want on just because of the looks. The isolation is the best I've felt in earphones below $30 and actually this pair cost me $10 when purchased. The sound quality is not amazing, but for the price they sound good, comparable with the classic Panasonic ones but with extra bass, without being too immersive in the lows. And they also feel more durable than the Panasonic ones and than Skullcandy earphones below $25. For this price, I highly recommend this earphones for on the go (got them in my bag), office, and gifts for family and friends. Will be buying a couple of earphones more for gifts and to have a backup.

title: Sound good, seem well made
content: I purchased these for an MP3 player (AGPtek A20) to use instead of the uncomfortable set that came with it.  The player turns off the back-light after 20 seconds or so, at which point it seems to go into a sort of "semi-sleep" mode.  You can still listen but can't adjust anything without powering it back up, unless you have the inline control. So my comments here relate to how I found these earbuds work with this particular player.  The volume feature works well.  The pause/play will only work when the back-light is on.  The "mic" feature isn't relevant in this case. (See "edit" below for next/previous feature.)  The sound is better than you would expect for the price.  The cord is flat, not round & fairly long- in excess of 4 feet. They're supposed to come with 3 sets of tips - one pair each of S, M, L (although mine had a fourth set inside the little carrying bag). They also have a small shirt clip, but I can't anything about it as I haven't used it. They seem well made & sturdy enough although I haven't used them during anything strenuous. I plugged them into the laptop just to experiment- none of the inline features worked there, but as this is meant to be used with a phone, that wasn't really a surprise. I'm extremely satisfied with them so far. Edited to add-  the next track/previous track feature doesn't seem to work well with the AGPtek A20 player.  I also plugged these into my Sony Walkman NWZ series player & none of the inline functions work.  They still work as earbuds though & I'd recommend them based on the quality of the sound & the moderate price! Another thing to be aware of is they're not a good choice for sleeping in- at least not for side sleepers.  Even with the smallest tips, they stick too far out of the ear canal to be comfortable. The comfort level is fine otherwise.

title: Good solid headphones for the price
content: I wasn't expecting a lot from these headphones, but I'm pleasantly surprised. I listen to music a lot, but I recently got my tragus pierced so I can't wear my earbuds for a while. I needed some over the ear headphones. These are super comfortable and they feel really nice while wearing them and don't fall off. The volume doesn't get as loud as I would like, but it's decent. I just like to blast my music super loud so that's on me. The sound quality is pretty good other than there's really no bass. Like I said though i wasn't expecting a lot from these headphones, because they're only $30. But for $30 they're great. My daughter even took them from me and wouldn't give them back so guess I'll be getting another pair for her. She has regular headphones that she doesn't use, because they snag her hair. She's 7 so they'll pretty much fit anybody...also the color is really nice. It's not a color you see a lot and I really like it.
